canonical:
  title: 故門下侍中魏繼廷配享睿宗敎書
  author: 郭東珣
  language: lzh
  text: 王者之孝爲能饗其親人臣之榮在不掩爾善玆奉先之罔極乃錫寵之惟新三重大匡檢校太師守太保開府儀同三司門下侍中判使部事上柱國某淸儉鎭於一時儀刑重於百辟實斯民先覺惟顧命大臣屬英陵晏駕之時方睿考飛龍之旦親傳玉璽方贊鴻基至今搢紳之閒想昔風節者衆配享于廟有闕禮官之文追錄其功在予寡人之命適修大禘用賚明恩擧玆從祀之儀加以易名之典俾先王迪高后賢業益彰雖死日猶生年忠魂已格加贈忠烈公
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 故門下侍中魏繼廷配享睿宗敎書
  author: 郭東珣
  language: lzh
  text: 王者之孝。爲能饗其親。人臣之榮。在不掩爾善。玆奉先之罔極。乃錫寵之惟新。三重大匡檢校太師守太保開府儀同三司門下侍中判使部事，上柱國某。淸儉鎭於一時。儀刑重於百辟。實斯民先覺。惟顧命大臣。屬英陵晏駕之時。方睿考飛龍之旦。親傳玉璽。方贊鴻基。至今搢紳之閒。想昔風節者衆。配享于廟。有闕禮官之文。追錄其功。在予寡人之命。適修大禘。用賚明恩。擧玆從祀之儀。加以易名之典。俾先王迪高后。賢業益彰。雖死日猶生年。忠魂已格。加贈忠烈公。
korean:
  title: 고 문하시중 위계정을 예종께 배향하는 교서
  author: 곽동순
  language: kor
  text: 왕자(王者)의 효도는 그 어버이를 향사(享祀)하는 데 있고, 신하의 영광은 그 착한 것을 드러내어 주는 데 있다. 이에 선왕(先王)을 받드는 망극한 마음에서, 죽은 신하에게 새로운 은전을 내려준다.삼중대광 검교태사 수태보개부의동삼사 문하시중 판이부사 상주국(三重大匡檢校太師守太保開府儀同三司門下侍中判吏部事上柱國) 모(某)는 맑고 검소한 것은 한 시대의 풍속을 진정시켰고, 아름다운 의표는 백관의 모범이 되었는 바, 실로 이 백성들의 선각(先覺)이요, 고명(顧命)을 받은 대신이었다. 영릉(英陵)이 승하하고 예고(睿考)가 즉위하던 날을 당하여 친히 옥새를 전하여 큰 기업(基業)을 도왔으므로 지금까지 사대부들 사이에는 지난날의 모와 절개를 회상하는 자가 많다.묘정(廟廷)에 배향하는 것을 당초에 예관(禮官)이 빠뜨렸으나, 그 공적을 추록(追錄)하는 것은 과인의 명에 있다. 마침 대제(大祭)를 행할 때를 당하여 은전을 내려 준다. 종사(從祀)하는 의례(儀禮)를 행하고 시호를 내리는 은전을 더한다. 선왕으로 하여금 고후(高后)를 따르게 하였으니 어진 사업이 더욱 나타났고, 비록 죽었을지라도 산 때와 같으리니 충혼(忠魂)이 이미 이르렀을 것이다. 충렬공(忠烈公) 시호를 내려 주노라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0260_020_0190&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Edict Conferring Ancestral Rites at the Shrine of Seongjong upon the Late Minister Wei Gyejeong
  author: Gwak Dong-sun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The filial piety of a king lies in honoring his forebears at their shrine; the glory of a subject lies in having his virtue revealed and exalted. Thus, moved by boundless devotion to the former king, we bestow new honors upon this departed minister.

    The late Three-Ranked Grand Commandant, Concurrent Grand Preceptor, Right Grand Tutor, Commandant of the Palace, Minister of the Palace Gate, Supervisor of the Ministry of Personnel, and Senior Pillar of State—this worthy soul was pure and frugal, steadying the customs of his age, his bearing and deportment the model for all officials. Truly was he the first awakened among the people, a great minister entrusted with the regency. When the sovereign of the English Mausoleum ascended to heaven and our wise predecessor took the dragon throne, he personally transmitted the jade seal and aided in the establishment of the great dynasty. To this day, among the scholars and officials, many recall his virtue and integrity of old.

    Though the ceremonial officers initially omitted his enshrinement at the ancestral temple, the recording of his merit falls within our command. Now, as we perform the great sacrifice, we bestow our benevolent grace. We institute the rites of his attendance at the shrine and add the honor of a posthumous name. Thus does the former king follow in the footsteps of the High Ancestress, and his worthy legacy shines ever brighter. Though his body has returned to dust, his spirit endures as in life—his loyal soul has already ascended. We hereby confer upon him the posthumous title of Lord of Loyal Excellence.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This is an official edict (敎書) from the Korean court, likely from the reign of Seongjong of Joseon, conferring honors and ancestral rites upon a deceased high official.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'English Mausoleum' (영릉) and 'wise predecessor' (예고) refer to the succession from one king to his successor.
  - key: ''
    value: The transmission of the jade seal symbolizes the peaceful transfer of royal authority.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'High Ancestress' (高后) may refer to a venerated royal consort or queen mother in the ancestral shrine.
